Description: Corroded copper alloy blade of quadrangular, long and flat shape, with a narrow straight head at one end, larger, thicker and bevelled on both sides at the other end, to form a cutting edge, now broken and irregular; possibly a chisel or an axe blade.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19 A
Curator's comments: bronze "chisel" "found in chamber 19A", with a "duplicate...kept at Bulak", mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 25. The Bulak duplicate is Cairo, EG, JE 27368.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 25)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.75, p.184, pl.26)
